nt; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5943.jpg" alt="" style="left: -80px;"> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_5991.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6027.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><li class="amazingcarousel-item" style="display: block; position: relative; background-image: none; background-color: transparent; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; float: left; width: 150px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-item-container" style="position: relative; margin: 0px 2px;"><div class="amazingcarousel-image"> <a href="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" title="" class="html5lightbox" data-group="amazingcarousel"> <img src="&#10;https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/IMG_6045.jpg" alt=""> </a><div class="amazingcarousel-hover-effect" style="display:none;position:absolute;left:0;top:0;width:100%;height:100%;cursor:pointer;background-image:url('https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/hoveroverlay-64-64-6.png');background-repeat:no-repeat;background-position:center center;"></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-title"></div></div></li><div style="clear:both;"></div></ul></div></div><div class="amazingcarousel-prev" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) left top no-repeat; display: block;"></div><div class="amazingcarousel-next" style="overflow: hidden; position: absolute; cursor: pointer; width: 32px; height: 32px; background: url(&quot;https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/slider/skins/arrows-32-32-1.png&quot;) right top no-repeat; display: block;"></div></div></div></div></div><p><strong>The popularity of this model among brides is because it reflects almost all following fashion trends:</strong></p><ul><li>a delicate elastic top with embroidery;</li><li>a built-in bra or cut-off cups;</li><li>a tender silhouette of a lace dress;</li><li>an open back and a short lacing on air loops;</li><li>and a full detachable skirt with a train.</li></ul><p><strong>This course contains a lot of couture techniques. I will show you the following:</strong></p><ul><li>how to seamlessly cover the corset with lace;</li><li>how to join a lace folded skirt to a dress, so that you don’t have any extra thickness and the transition from a corset to a dress is smooth and invisible;</li><li>how to sew an elastic top between a face and a lining;</li><li>how to make a lining with built-in cups.</li></ul><p><strong>The special feature of the course is tambour (luneville) sequin embroidery.</strong></p><p>The process of cutting, sewing and decoration of a garment from scratch to final operations is described and illustrated in detail.<br> All necessary patterns and bonuses (for printing) are attached as follows:</p><ul><li>2 tables for AUTOMATIC pattern adjustments calculation for all patterns of this course;</li><li>patterns of a corset face and a corset lining;</li><li>patterns of decorative details.</li></ul><div><p><strong>The aim of the course</strong>&nbsp;is my great desire to teach the techniques of making such dresses. All the techniques can be used in various combinations, so that you can sew different models of evening, cocktail, prom and wedding dresses.</p><p><strong>The course is useful</strong>&nbsp;both to beginners as well as to experienced professionals in making wedding and evening dresses. It can be handy for dressmaking atelier personnel as a professional development training.</p></div><div></div><div><p><strong>Author:</strong>&nbsp;Tatiana Kozorovitsky</p><p><strong>Total length:</strong>&nbsp;6h 45m</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="transcript"><div class="overlay"></div><div itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"> <span itemprop="publisher" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Organization"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy"> <span itemprop="logo" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="name" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="text" content="Corset Academy logo"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="https://www.facebook.com/corsetacademy"> </span> <span itemprop="author" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/Person"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tatiana Kozorovitsky"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/uploads/MVI_3285.MOV.00_00_31_09.Still001-128x128.jpg"><meta itemprop="width" content="128"><meta itemprop="height" content="128"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/jpeg"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/author/infocorsetacademy-net/"><meta itemprop="sameAs" content="http://www.corsetacademy.net"> </span><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-22-tools-and-materials-for-embroidery/"><meta itemprop="mainEntityOfPage" content="https://corsetacademy.net/tutorial-22-tools-and-materials-for-embroidery/"><meta itemprop="datePublished" content="2018-12-03T20:46:26+00:00"><meta itemprop="dateModified" content="2018-12-03T20:46:26+00:00"><meta itemprop="copyrightYear" content="2018"><meta itemprop="inLanguage" content="en_US"><meta itemprop="name" content="Tutorial 22. Tools and materials for embroidery."><meta itemprop="headline" content="Tutorial 22. Tools and materials for embroidery."><meta itemprop="description" content="I prepared all materials for decoration of the top - for its embroidery. As the pattern is quite large we need to use a wide embroidery frame suitable for large fabric strip"><meta itemprop="articleSection" content="Wedding Dress with Detachable Full Skirt. Part 1."><meta itemprop="keywords" content="wedding dress with detachable full skirt. part 1., video"> <span itemprop="image" itemscope="" itemtype="http://schema.org/ImageObject"><meta itemprop="url" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="contentUrl" content="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset/img/logo.png"><meta itemprop="width" content="303"><meta itemprop="height" content="49"><meta itemprop="encodingFormat" content="image/png"> </span><div itemprop="articleBody"><h1>Tutorial 22. Tools and materials for embroidery.</h1><p><strong>The pattern of the top is traced on the paper.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image002.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I prepared all materials for preliminary decoration of the top - for its embroidery.</strong></p><p>As the pattern is quite large we need to use a wide embroidery frame suitable for large fabric strip.</p><p>I do not plan to have much embroidery as it is not necessary to overload the top with the extra decoration as the main accent should be on the dress, for example, its lace detachable train.</p><p>That is why I will do embroidery on the main contours and sleeves.</p><p><strong>As the pattern is large we need to get a wider embroidery frame.&nbsp; </strong></p><p>Certainly, there are plenty professional frames of large size and modifications, but they are quite expensive too.</p><p>In my opinion, it is worth buying such frame if you plan to embroider at the industrial scale.</p><p><strong>I would like to share an idea how you can make such frame.</strong></p><p><strong>As a base I used the school kids’ board, which is available in IKEA.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image004.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>For the frame I prepared 4 wooden bars 118 cm long, 4 cm wide and 1,5 cm thick. </strong>I made slots on two bars and drilled holes in 5 cm from each other. All the figures are conditional and the main idea is that all is symmetrical. I attached double folded thick and loose fabric similar to thick woolen cloth on the wooden bars with the slots by a staple gun.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image006.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Beside, for narrower fabrics I also prepared two 40 cm long bars with the symmetrical slots.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image008.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>To fix the frame you need to have bolts or bolts with double thumbscrews.</strong> Besides it is convenient to use additional bolts as a stand for spool of thread.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image010.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I will describe the use of the frame and how to fill in the fabric during next tutorials. </strong></p><p><strong>Now, let us review the necessary tools and materials. </strong></p><p><strong>It is necessary to have a spinner for beads or sequins threading.</strong> I recommend buying a wooden professional spinner. You will not be able to do a well-balanced spinner with bearings yourself and it will be impossible to thread lots of glass beads, beads and sequins! &nbsp;There are special curved long needles in the set with a spinner. Thread is inserted in one end of the needle and the other end is inserted into a spinner. When a spinner is spun the needle is thread with the materials you put into a spinner.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image012.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>Now we talk about the main tools for embroidery – the hooks. </strong></p><p><strong>I know three main types of hooks, which we may use for the tambour embroidery.&nbsp; Firstly, it is a Luneville hook.</strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image014.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>This is the most famous and the most popular hook. </strong>Practically, everyone who starts to study tambour embroidery take the Luneville hook as it is believed that Luneville embroidery should be made with this particular hook.</p><p><strong>In fact, Luneville embroidery is nothing more than tambour embroidery! </strong>I will not discuss long whether it is worth mastering the Luneville hook. <strong>But, in order to master tambour embroidery with the Luneville hook, you need diligence and a lot of time.</strong> Nothing happens at once! You need to work hard and long, sitting and making the directions with this hook. You must learn, at first simply, to make a continuous square in 4 directions, without turning the framed garment, make a circle, eight-curve and various types of zigzag and a filling. And only after, when you confidently begin to embroider these figures without beads in small steps with the Luneville hook, you will need to repeat with beads and sequins.</p><p><strong>Moreover, you still have to train to work with different materials: </strong>you must be able to confidently sew with large and small beads, you must understand and feel how to hold the thread, so that it does not stretch, but at the same time, and the loop does not go off the hook<strong>.</strong></p><p><strong>But that's not all: </strong>not every thread is suitable for the Luneville embroidery with the Luneville hook! The Luneville hook is a professional hook and it is very sharp and thin enough to split the wrong type of thread.</p><p><strong>And yet, have you known that you can only embroider with the Luneville hook on the underside or when the drawing is underneath. </strong>In other words, you can see only the seam that goes on the wrong side, and the sequins or beads are on the face. Without skills, just looking through the transparent mesh, and if it's some curtain veil, organza or chiffon, you only see the thread and the outline of the materials that you are embroidering. You cannot always turn the framed garment to check the quality of work<strong>.</strong></p><p><strong>Therefore, the Luneville hook is for professional embroiderers! </strong>It is for the experienced embroiderer who has already spent hours and days of work with such hook.</p><p><strong>Of course, the Luneville hook has a lot of advantages! </strong>That's why the professionals are embroidering with this hook. But, we are the specialists of wide range of qualifications! We need to be able to do everything: to strass, to make appliques, to cover corsets without cutting, and to drape, and yet, to cut and to sew and plus to embroider.</p><p><strong>That's it for such specialists like you and me 2 more wonderful hooks were invented!</strong></p><p><strong>Firstly, it is the Clover hook.</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image016.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>The feature of this hook is the spring latch.</strong></p><p><strong>You need to be careful and not to mix the Clover hook with the cheap Chinese hook to raise loops!</strong> These hooks are not suitable for our embroidery! I am telling you that, so you will not be tempted to save money! Please, buy high-quality tools.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image018.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>The Clover hook should only be the original Clover hook!</strong></p><p><strong>I fell in love with this hook from the first minute I purchased it!</strong></p><p><strong>And, here are the advantages.</strong></p><p><strong>- </strong>thanks to the latch on the hook, you will learn how to use it within one day, I guarantee! When working with this hook, unlike the Luneville one, you do not need to spend an insane amount of time learning: you will embroider a square, a circle, an eight-circle and a filling without beads from the first time. After training how to throw off the thread from the hook, for embroidery with beads or sequins, you spend a little more time, but not that much!</p><p>- one more important circumstance - you can embroider from above as well as from below, it is absolutely equivalent. The only thing you have to learn is one rule that I will explain.</p><p>Of course, <strong>the Clover hook</strong> has some disadvantages, but they are insignificant compared to the advantages:</p><p>- this hook is flat, therefore, when piercing a thin fabric or fine, it can tear the fabric. In other words, the hole from this hook becomes larger than the mesh.</p><p>- the spring on the latch may break.</p><p><strong>But in the course I would like to show you one more hook, the American one, which is invented and sold in the USA.</strong></p><p><strong>This is the real professional hook for tambour embroidery!</strong></p><p><strong>The American hook has the same qualities as the Clover hook. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image020.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>Unlike the Clover hook the American hook is thin and sharp! </strong>It does not leave any holes and you can work with it from above and from below.</p><p><strong>The American hook makes the same tambour embroidery like the Luneville hook, but you will spend a day or two to learn how to use it. </strong></p><p><strong>I will show you the method of using it.</strong> You do not need to turn or rotate the hook during the embroidery to hook thread like you do with the Luneville hook. It is much simpler! The only thing you should know is the rule to go in and out of fabric and the direction of the hook during embroidery. And I will demonstrate it.</p><p><strong>Moreover, thread requirements are much simpler for the Clover hook and the American hook for tambour embroidery. </strong>In fact, you can embroider with any thread! Of course, I still recommend using for embroidery strong threads - extra or ultra. This recommendation is based on the fact that a glass bead, which can have sharp edges, should not rub the thread.</p><p><strong>And now, let us talk about the threads.</strong></p><p><strong>My favorite thread is the thread made by the French firm Broder Plizere, on the website of which I have bought these threads and a Lunevil hook. </strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image022.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>This thread is strong enough, rather thin, and most importantly, it is splendidly twisted! </strong>Besides it is 100% cotton! Besides, I need to say that this is the only thread with which you can work absolutely without problems with the Luneville hook! And for the Clover and the American hooks - this is the best option!</p><p><strong>I also prefer to work with the French MADAME TRICOTE threads</strong>. It is sold in sewing stores in Israel.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image024.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>This is 100 % polyester thread and it is strong and well-twisted. </strong>It is also well suitable for the Clover and the American hooks.</p><p><strong>I think that it is clear which threads can be used for embroidery, trust me, there are plenty of them. Try to use different threads and select the most suitable for you. &nbsp;</strong></p><p><strong><br> <img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image026.png" alt=""></strong></p><p><strong>For framing I recommend using the shoe thread. </strong></p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image028.png" alt=""></p><p>This is the super strong thread, but its advantage is that it is waxed and it does not get tangled and it does not tear the thin fabric. I use the 0,5 mm thick thread.</p><p><strong>There are some more tools necessary for our work.</strong></p><p><strong>For tracing of the drawing I use the write-erase pens. </strong>It is better to use the Pilot pens.</p><p>The Gutermann textile glue is needed for strengthening the knots at the beginning and the end of the embroidery for the final fixing.</p><p><strong>Scissors for embroidery.</strong></p><p><strong>Rectangular ruler for the tracing.</strong> You will see how I use this ruler further.</p><p><strong>What will we embroider on our top? </strong></p><p><strong>This time – the sequins will be mostly used. </strong>I will use 6 mm and 4 mm transparent silver-coated sequins of and 4 mm white sequins.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image030.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I suggest making embroidery on a Dutch bobbinet.</strong> It is a white fine mesh fabric, which stretches crosswise and it is rather non-stretchable lengthwise.</p><p><img class="img-responsive center-block" src="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/transcripts/Tutorial%2022.files/image032.png" alt=""></p><p><strong>I think that I have named all materials. </strong></p><p><strong>This time I will use the American hook for tambour embroidery. </strong>Before start I will show you all methods of work with this hook.</p></div></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="pattern"><p>Sewing patterns are in PDF format. To print sewing patterns open the files, press “print” and choose&nbsp;<strong>“print in actual size”</strong>. In each&nbsp;file the pattern is divided &nbsp;to A4 paper sheets for home printers.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Automatic Pattern Alterations Calculator:</strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGcorset/corset.htm" target="_blank">The Dress (Corset)</a></strong></h4><h4><strong><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/calculations/ENGskirt/ENGskirt.htm" target="_blank">The Skirt</a></strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><p>&nbsp;</p> <a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/belt%2C%20bow.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Belf and The Bow</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20front.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Front</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/corset%20-%20lining.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> Corset Lining</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/pattern.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Pattern</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/skirt.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Skirt</a><br><a href="https://corsetacademy.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wedding%20dresses/wedding_11/patterns/top.pdf" target="_blank" class=""><img src="https://cdn.shortpixel.ai/client/q_glossy,ret_img/https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/pdf.png"> The Top</a><br></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="diploma"><div class="dark-get-started margin-0"><p>In order to receive the Corset Academy graduation diploma you need to submit your graduation work.<br> Upload the photo of the garment that you made after completing the course.<br> I will personally review your work.<br> After the approval you will receive a personalized diploma to your email box, no longer than within 1 business day.</p><p class="text-right">Tatiana Kozorovitsky.</p><form id="diplomaForm"><h4>Your datails:</h4><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="firstname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter first name" required=""><p class="firstname error">Enter your first name</p></div><div class="form-group"> <input type="text" id="lastname" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter last name" required=""><p class="lastname error">Enter your last name</p></div><h4>Choose a course:</h4><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option1" value="1"> <label for="option1"> <em>Wedding gowns design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option2" value="2"> <label for="option2"> <em>Evening dresses design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><div class="radio"> <input type="radio" name="course" id="option3" value="3"> <label for="option3"> <em>Corsetry design and sewing course.</em> </label></div><p class="course error margin-10-bottom">Select course</p><div class="form-group"> <label class="uploadbutton"><div class="button">Choose file</div><div class="pull-left"><div class="input">No file selected</div></div> <input type="file" id="fileupload" name="files[]" data-url="https://corsetacademy.net/diploma/upload/"> </label><div id="progress" class="progress" style="display: none;"><div class="bar progress-bar progress-bar-warning progress-bar-striped active" role="progressbar" style="width: 0%;"></div></div> <input type="hidden" id="uploadDataUrl"><p class="upload error">Please upload photo of your work.</p><p>Max file size 2 Mb</p></div> <input type="hidden" id="userEmail" value="ngochuy.mmt@gmail.com"> <button id="submitDiploma" type="submit" class="btn btn-green-simple">Submit</button><h3 id="submitSpinner" class="text-center" style="display:none"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-spin"></i></h3></form><h4 id="statusAnswer" class="text-center"></h4><div class="clearfix"></div><h3 class="get-pro text-center">The example of the diploma:</h3> <a href="https://corsetacademy.net/wp-content/themes/corset-rs/img/diploma_example.png" class="wplightbox" title="Diploma Example"><div id="diploma_example"></div> </a></div></div><div role="tabpanel" class="tab-pane" id="faq"><p class="text-center"><i class="fa fa-spinner fa-pulse fa-3x"></i></p></div></div></div></div>

 @endsection